CP_AL

Copyright 2026 Benqi Liu.

This repository contains the CP_AL implementation used for the linear
programming experiments in the paper "Restarted Reflected Halpern
Acceleration for Augmented Primal--Dual Methods".

The main additions in this distribution include the CP_AL augmented
primal--dual update, generic restart and augmentation controllers, an
identity-free matrix-feature equilibration rule, benchmark scripts, and
release documentation. The released benchmark policy does not dispatch on a
benchmark name, data-set path, split, tolerance, or instance identity.

Some low-level GPU solver infrastructure is adapted from Apache-2.0 licensed
first-order optimization software. The CP_AL algorithmic components, feature
policy, release scripts, and documentation in this distribution are provided
as Benqi Liu's research implementation. Original third-party copyright and
license notices are retained in the corresponding source files.

